examination /ɪɡˌzæmɪˈneɪʃən/

(examinations) 

1. N-COUNT An examination is a formal test that you take to show your knowledge or ability in a particular subject, or to obtain a qualification. 考试 [正式] 

例： ...college examination results. …大学考试成绩。 

2.  →  see also examine 

3. N-COUNT If you have a medical examination , a doctor looks at your body, feels it, or does simple tests in order to check how healthy you are. (健康状况) 检查 

例： You must see your doctor for a thorough examination. 你必须去看医生，做个全面体检。

